## Main Features

- Expressive MIDI chord generation
- Editable piano-roll preview
- Direct writing into the selected MIDI clip
- Root and scale selection
- Engine and color controls
- Bars, octave, velocity and spread settings
- Complexity and expressiveness control
- Bass Root option
- Top Line option
- Smooth inversions
- Human Feel timing variation
- Arpeggiator mode
- Arp rate and pattern controls
- Randomize function
- Create Chords button

## Workflow

1. Select a MIDI clip in Ableton Live.
2. Open GRAV DUCK from the Ableton Live Extensions menu.
3. Choose Root, Scale, Engine and Color.
4. Adjust Bars, Octave, Velocity, Spread, Complexity and Express.
5. Enable Bass Root, Top Line, Inversions, Human Feel or Arpeggiator if needed.
6. Preview the chord structure visually in the piano-roll.
7. Click Create Chords to write the result into the selected MIDI clip.

## Design Philosophy

GRAV DUCK was created to simplify my own workflow inside Ableton Live.

It is not built as a commercial product or a marketing project.  
It started as a personal tool to create harmonic ideas faster, explore MIDI generation, and understand what the Ableton Live 12 Extensions SDK can do.

If the tool can be useful to other producers, I am happy to share it.  
If it is not useful, not stable enough, or not interesting for the community, I completely understand.

This project is still experimental and shared mainly for feedback, learning and creative exploration.

